content:
Creating an HTML page to summarize "Sapiens: A Graphic Novel" by Yuval Noah Harari based on a review from The New York Times involves structuring the content with clear sections, using visual elements to enhance readability, and including relevant links. Below is a simple HTML template:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Sapiens: A Graphic Novel - Book Review Summary</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            background-color: #f4f4f9;
            color: #333;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }
        header {
            background-color: #555;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 10px 0;
            text-align: center;
        }
        main {
            padding: 20px;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: auto;
        }
        h1, h2 {
            color: #444;
        }
        p {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        a {
            color: #1a73e8;
            text-decoration: none;
        }
        a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }
        footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 10px 0;
            background-color: #555;
            color: #fff;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
    <h1>Sapiens: A Graphic Novel</h1>
    <p>Book Review Summary</p>
</header>

<main>
    <section>
        <h2>Overview of the Book</h2>
        <p>"Sapiens: A Graphic Novel" is an adaptation of Yuval Noah Harari's acclaimed book "Sapiens: A Brief History of Humankind." This visual retelling explores the history of humankind from the Stone Age to the modern era, making complex historical and scientific concepts accessible and engaging through stunning illustrations and storytelling.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Author's Writing Style</h2>
        <p>Yuval Noah Harari is known for his insightful and thought-provoking writing style. His ability to distill complex ideas into accessible narratives is preserved in the graphic novel format, complemented by vivid illustrations that enhance the reader's understanding and engagement.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Potential Audience</h2>
        <p>This graphic novel appeals to a wide audience, including history enthusiasts, graphic novel aficionados, and anyone interested in understanding the journey of humankind in a visually engaging format. It serves as an excellent introduction for readers new to Harari's work while providing a fresh perspective for existing fans.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Relevant Resources</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="https://www.ynharari.com" target="_blank">Yuval Noah Harari's Official Website</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://twitter.com/harari_yuval" target="_blank">Yuval Noah Harari on Twitter</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.nytimes.com" target="_blank">The New York Times</a></li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</main>

<footer>
    <p>&copy; 2023 Book Review Summary. All rights reserved.</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
```

### Key Elements:
- **Structure**: The page is divided into sections with headings for easy navigation.
- **Design**: Simple and clean styling with a focus on readability.
- **Links**: Provides easy access to related resources.
- **Responsiveness**: The layout is responsive, ensuring it displays well on different devices. 

You can expand on this template by adding images, more detailed content, and additional styling to suit your preferences.
